   83: ## Scope-control rule
   84: Every new idea is classified as one of four types:
   85: ```text
   86: A. Core v0                — necessary for the first coherent version of the model.
   87: B. Extension v1+          — useful, but not required for the first model.
   88: C. Country implementation — depends on legal/administrative/political choices of an implementing country.
   89: D. Out of scope           — not necessary for the model and should not be solved now.
   90: ```
   91: The project should not keep expanding unless a new idea is clearly Core v0 or a serious objection that
   92: threatens the core model.
   93: 
   94: ## Operating rule
   95: After every significant conversation or review round: (1) distill new concepts; (2) create/update
   96: hypotheses/docs; (3) record objections; (4) update open questions; (5) classify new ideas by scope;
   97: (6) communicate with the user in Spanish; (7) write durable repository documents in English; (8) include
   98: concrete examples from the case under review; (9) revise the roadmap before every commit and whenever
   99: the strategy changes.

