  542: traceability as **conditional outputs of that apparatus**, but are **superseded
  543: for magnitude inference** and are no longer offered as the paper's headline.
  544: 
  545: **Quantitative status (governing).** A pre-registered, symmetric, selection-only
  546: stress test — both arms with matched expected appraisal-report budgets, the same
  547: candidate pool, costs and noise, delivery at parity, each acting on its own noisy
  548: estimate rather than ground truth — found the distributed-minus-central selection
  549: advantage **positive in every one of 18 pre-specified cells but small.** The
  550: pre-registered decision statistic is the **pooled median Δ = 0.025**, below the
  551: pre-registered **0.05 research-program rebuild gate**; a **post-hoc** ratio-of-sums estimate is
  552: **Δ = 0.026, with a 95% world-cluster Monte-Carlo interval [0.023, 0.029]**
  553: (reported separately, on the simulated data-generating process). The compound
  554: multiplier is therefore **not** claimed as a calibrated effect. This is a stylized
  555: test of a *selection mechanism*, not a validated implementation of Core v0: its
  556: value and credit variables are abstract scores, not measured visibility,
  557: traceability, permanence, or public value. The **0.05** figure is a
  558: research-program **rebuild threshold** on this uncalibrated scale (a go/no-go rule
  559: for whether to pursue a quantitative rebuild), **not** a calibrated policy-materiality
  560: threshold. The controlling specification is
  561: [claim-and-estimand-contract](../research/claim-and-estimand-contract.md); the test,
  562: its frozen pre-registration, results, and diagnostics are
  563: `scripts/simulation/e5-sp-symmetry-gate.mjs` and `audits/2026-07-10/symmetry-gate-*`.
  564: The load-bearing contributions are the architecture and the mechanism *direction*,
  565: not a point multiplier.
  566: 
  567: **The symmetric credit-versus-coverage gate (methods and result).** Because this
  568: is the paper's one confirmatory computation, its design is stated in full here
  569: rather than only by reference. Each world holds K = 500 candidate projects; for
  570: each, N = 5000 potential participants are considered, each interested with a
  571: project-specific probability, so the interested reach is at most N and endogenous.
  572: Both arms then see the
  573: same candidate pool, the same exact costs, the same truth net[j] = S[j] − h·cost[j],
  574: delivery held at **parity**, and the same report noise report = v + Normal(0, τ);
  575: each funds a **greedy** set under a budget of one-third of total project cost, is
  576: eligible to fund a project only where *its own* noisy estimate of net is positive
  577: (no oracle gate), and its delivered value is scored on the projects' *true* net.
  578: The arms are symmetric except for the coverage mechanism and its matched
  579: counterparts. *Distributed (endogenous coverage):* each interested citizen reports
  580: independently with probability p if her value v ≥ 0 and p·(1 − β) if v < 0 (adverse
  581: voice bias), giving ĥS_D = Σreports / p, ranked by estimated net per cost.
  582: *Central (competent value-reader):* an appraisal budget matched to the distributed
  583: arm's *expected* total reports in that world, spread **evenly** across projects as a
  584: rounded fixed per-project bandwidth m_C = round(expected reports / K) (so the two
  585: arms' appraisal totals are equal in expectation up to that rounding); per project it
  586: samples m_C interested citizens, observes v + Normal(0, τ), and forms its own noisy
  587: ĥNet_C = reach·mean(observed) − h·cost. It ranks by score = (1 − λ)·z(ĥNet_C/cost) + λ·z(P/cost) — its **own noisy
  588: estimate**, never the true net — where P is claimable political credit (the
  589: electoral credit-claiming and traceability logic by which visible, attributable
  590: benefits are favoured over diffuse ones; Mayhew 1974; Arnold 1990) and λ is bounded
  591: credit pressure (a *posited* pressure whose real-world magnitude must be measured,
  592: not assumed). Credit moves *ranking*, never eligibility (no knowingly
  593: value-destroying planner). The legitimate asymmetries are therefore only these:
  594: distributed reports self-route to projects citizens care about while negative
  595: stakeholders participate less, and central appraisal is spread evenly while its
  596: ranking carries credit pressure — everything else is shared. The estimand is
  597: **Δ = (D − C)/O** per world, where D, C, O are delivered true net for the
  598: distributed, central, and full-information greedy arms and O is a reference level,
  599: not an optimum. The frozen grid sweeps λ ∈ {0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3} (λ = 0 a negative
  600: control), a latent-correlation setting ρ ∈ {0, 0.5, 1} (realized corr(S, P) ≈ 0.00,
  601: 0.30, 0.82), and h ∈ {1.5, 2.5, 4} over 100 seeded worlds, in a baseline
  602: observation regime (p = .35, β = .30, τ = .5) and a matched-budget low-information
  603: stress regime (p = .15, β = .60, τ = 1.0). The **pre-registered decision rule** —
  604: frozen before running and designed by the independent auditor to be adversarial —
  605: required, for a GO on rebuilding the quantitative engine, at least 15 of the 18
  606: primary cells with mean Δ > 0, a pooled **median Δ ≥ 0.05**, a bootstrap lower
  607: bound > 0, and median Δ ≥ 0 under the stress regime, plus a guard to pause if the
  608: λ = 0 control itself exceeded 0.05. The result was **NO-GO**: the advantage was
  609: positive in all 18 primary cells, but the pre-registered pooled **median Δ = 0.025**,
  610: below the 0.05 rebuild gate; the λ = 0 negative control sat at ≈ 0.016, within the
  611: pause guard (no hidden asymmetry flagged). A **post-hoc** world-cluster
  612: ratio-of-sums estimate was Δ = 0.026 [0.023, 0.029] (Monte-Carlo uncertainty on the
  613: simulated data-generating process, reported separately from the median). The
  614: advantage rises with credit pressure λ and falls as credit aligns with value — the
  615: credit-versus-coverage mechanism — but it is small, which is why the calibrated
  616: multiplier is retired and the paper rests on the architecture and the mechanism
  617: direction.
  618: 
