  988: **Finding 7: an audit-parameterized baseline — what it does and does not
  989: calibrate.** The manuscript-review round's sharpest attack held that the zero-control
  990: baseline is a caricature — real administrations run audit institutions,
  991: retentions, bonds, and inspection — and the answer was a seventh
  992: pre-registered experiment (`research/e7-calibrated-baseline-design.md`)
  993: with a committed withdrawal condition: if the headline collapsed against
  994: a fair baseline, it would be withdrawn, not requalified. The
  995: audit-parameterized status-quo arm draws its parameters from published
