    Round-5 remediation: gate-block exactness, E7 provenance reconciliation, forward-stable roadmap
    
    Clear the three non-author-gated residuals from the round-5 verification:
    
    1. Gate block exactness (EN+ES): "N = 5000 potential participants considered per
       project, interested reach at most N and endogenous" (not "up to N drawn"); central
       bandwidth stated as the rounded fixed m_C = round(expected reports / K), totals
       equal in expectation up to rounding.
    2. E7 provenance: reconcile the design doc's "queue must clear" precondition with E7's
       demoted Path-B status — E7 figures are conditional apparatus outputs (not a
       confirmatory/verified result), the primary-source queue is documented incomplete and
       off the publication critical path; soften the paper's remaining "audit-documented"
       -> "audit-reported (verification ongoing)" (EN+ES); fix the design-doc banner stat to
       median 0.025.
    3. Roadmap single state: make docs/03 + remediation-roadmap forward-stable (highest-
       numbered audit round is authoritative; no round-specific "in progress" that goes
       stale); fix the remaining "0.05 materiality bar" -> rebuild gate; correct the
       live-title fix from "needs a redeposit" to "direct metadata edit, no new DOI".
    
    check-anchors clean; EN/ES parity (13/13); git diff --check clean.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

